# Socketmap Service Configuration Example
# Copy this to .env and update with your values

# ==============================================
# Server Configuration
# ==============================================

# Listen address (0.0.0.0 for all interfaces, 127.0.0.1 for localhost only)
SOCKETMAP_HOST=0.0.0.0

# Listen port
SOCKETMAP_PORT=9100

# ==============================================
# Thunder IDP Configuration
# ==============================================

# Thunder server hostname (use Docker service name in compose)
THUNDER_HOST=thunder-server

# Thunder server port
THUNDER_PORT=8090

# Sample Application ID from Thunder setup (OPTIONAL)
# If not set, will be automatically extracted from thunder-setup container logs
# Get this from: docker logs thunder-setup 2>&1 | grep 'Sample App ID:'
THUNDER_SAMPLE_APP_ID=

# ==============================================
# Cache Configuration
# ==============================================

# Cache TTL in seconds (how long to cache results)
# Recommended: 300 (5 min) for dev, 600 (10 min) for prod
CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=300

# Token refresh interval in seconds
# Thunder tokens typically last 1 hour, refresh at 55 minutes
TOKEN_REFRESH_SECONDS=3300

# ==============================================
# Automatic Sample App ID Extraction
# ==============================================
# 
# The socketmap service will automatically extract the Sample App ID
# from the thunder-setup container logs if THUNDER_SAMPLE_APP_ID is not set.
# 
# This eliminates the need to manually configure it!
# 
# ==============================================

# ==============================================
# Example Domain Structure in Thunder
# ==============================================
# 
# For domain: silver.openmail.lk
# 
# Create OUs in Thunder:
# 1. Root OU: openmail.lk
# 2. Child OU: silver (under openmail.lk)
# 
# API path: /organization-units/tree/openmail.lk/silver
# 
# ==============================================

# ==============================================
# Quick Start
# ==============================================
#
# 1. No need to set THUNDER_SAMPLE_APP_ID! 
#    It's automatically extracted from logs.
#
# 2. Build and run:
#    go build -o socketmap main.go
#    ./socketmap
#
# 3. Test:
#    echo "15:virtual-domains 16:silver.openmail.lk," | nc localhost 9100
#
# Expected output: "4:OK 1,"
#
